description: Originated 1595–1605 from Late Latin cooperatus (“work with”). See co- + operate. Displaced native Old English efnwyrċan.

verbs.description: cooperate (third-person singular simple present cooperates, present participle cooperating, simple past and past participle cooperated)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To work or act together, especially for a common purpose or benefit.
(intransitive) To allow for mutual unobstructed action
(intransitive) To function in harmony, side by side
